{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-3822"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Treatment and disposal of hazardous waste"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "3822"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :utilities/hazardous-waste-treatment-disposal
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:environmental-protection :public-health :chain-of-custody :regulatory-transparency]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :haz-waste-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics false
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "HazWasteTreatment-LLM (sealed advisor) ⊣ HazWasteGovernor (independent
  censor), a genuinely compiled langgraph-clj StateGraph
  (hazwaste.operation/build: :intake -> :advise -> :govern -> :decide
  -+-> :commit / :request-approval -> :commit / :hold, with
  `interrupt-before #{:request-approval}` + checkpointer for real
  human-in-the-loop resume on cross-border shipments). Eight governor
  checks (hazwaste.policy) gate every receive/execute/disclosure/dispute:
  rbac, manifest-chain-of-custody-gate and treatment-method-
  authorization-gate (domain-unique HARD checks — no analog in sibling
  actors), source-provenance-gate, licensed-disclosure, confidence
  floor, cross-border-gate, dispute-request-always-escalates. Tracks
  manifest chain-of-custody (generator -> transporter -> facility) and
  facility treatment-authorization state only — no field anywhere in
  the schema for physical transport routing or execution; this actor
  never arranges or dispatches a shipment itself, it only records and
  gates the regulatory record. Real regulatory-provenance catalog
  (hazwaste.facts): US EPA RCRA Subtitle C manifest system, EU Waste
  Shipment Regulation, Basel Convention movement documents — every
  asserted fact must cite one of these, none fabricated. Append-only
  audit ledger (hazwaste.store/ledger + append-ledger!), Store protocol
  with MemStore (default) and DatomicStore (langchain.db) backends
  proven to the same contract (store_contract_test.clj); DatomicStore's
  EDN-blob codec uses kotoba-lang/langchain-store's shared `ls/enc` /
  `ls/dec*` rather than a bespoke pr-str/edn-read-string pair.
  Phase 0->3 staged-autonomy gate (hazwaste.phase), default-phase=1 from
  initial implementation, that can only narrow — never widen — what the
  governor already allows. 28 tests / 98 assertions green
  (`clojure -M:dev:test`), clj-kondo 0 errors/warnings
  (`clojure -M:lint`), demo runnable end-to-end (`clojure -M:dev:run`).
  Deliberately distinct from cloud-itonami-isic-3811 (non-hazardous
  waste collection): 3811 dispatches non-hazardous streams, this actor
  treats/disposes hazardous waste under RCRA Subtitle C / the EU Waste
  Shipment Regulation / the Basel Convention."}
